OL,4,Chearing on state covert surveillance
OL,5,Cclaims
OL,7,FMr McCaffrey said: "We feel that we
OL,8,Fneed to know, and journalists and
OL,9,Fsociety need to know, if police have
OL,10,Fbeen surveilling journalists for no
OL,11,Fother reason than we're doing our job.
OL,13,F"Journalism isn't a crime. Journalists
OL,14,Fshouldn't be treated as criminals or
OL,15,Fas criminal suspects, and if that is
OL,16,Fthe case, UK police have an awful lot
OL,17,Fto answer for.
